'''Grant Imahara''' was an [[Industrial Light & Magic]] modeler and animatronics technician who controlled [[R2-D2]]'s movements in the ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[prequel trilogy]]. Imahara cameoed in the mockumentary ''[[R2-D2: Beneath the Dome]]'', and was an actor and writer of the [[TheForce.net]] fan film [https://www.theforce.net/fanfilms/shortfilms/ilm-agents/index.asp ''Architects of Evil'']. The [[in-universe]] company [[Imaharatronics]] is named for him.

Grant Imahara was also known as the creator of the [[Wikipedia:Battlebots|Battlebot]] Deadblow and was a cast member on Discovery Channel's [[Wikipedia:MythBusters|''MythBusters'']], prior to a restructuring of the program.

On [[April 2]], [[2011]], Imahara was inducted into the [[501st Legion (fan organization)|501st Legion]] fan organization.<ref>{{Twitter|grantimahara|status/54574808163295233|Grant Imahara|quote=I was inducted into the @501stLegion at #WonderCon yesterday. It was a tremendous honor! Special thanks to Jedi @bonniegrrl!|archivedate=20200714193952}}</ref> He passed away following a brain aneurysm on [[July 13]], [[2020]].<ref name="Death" />

